  "text": "This performance can be also explained with distribution diagram for the DA species as a function of pH, where at pH values higher than 7, the concentration of the protonated form is present together the second specie and this probably difficult the incorporation in the negatively charged polymer [CITATION_1] . It is also illustrated by Scheme 3. Therefore, changed in the pH influences the peaks height, as expected on the basis of the pKa value; higher concentration of the protonated forms are present at lower pH that can be more easily incorporated in the cation exchanged polymer. As previously reported [CITATION_2] , lowering the pH results in the formation of protonated carbonium ions.",
